# VitePress Usage

Commands

- `npm run dev` — start local server
- `npm run build` — generate static site into `docs/.vitepress/dist`
- `npm run preview` — preview built site

Add a new series

1. Create `docs/series/<series-slug>/index.md` (overview with objectives & prerequisites)
2. Create `docs/series/<series-slug>/chapters/`
3. Create `docs/series/<series-slug>/code/`
4. Update `docs/.vitepress/config.ts` nav and sidebar entries

Add a chapter

1. Add `docs/series/<slug>/chapters/<nn>-<chapter-slug>.md`
2. Place larger code in `docs/series/<slug>/code/`
3. Reference files with relative links
4. Add chapter to the series sidebar

Deploy

- GitHub Actions builds and deploys to `gh-pages`.
- Ensure `base` in `config.ts` is `/PHP-From-Scratch/` for project pages.
